text: Boboszów () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Międzylesie, within Kłodzko County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland, near the border with the Czech Republic. It lies approximately south-east of Międzylesie, south of Kłodzko, and south of the regional capital Wrocław. The village has a population of 240. ==References== Category:Villages in Kłodzko County Category:Czech Republic–Poland border crossings
